Author: keiya-hattori
Title: [ANN] [ICO] Target Coin - World's FIRST And ONLY Bonus Paying Crypto Fund
Body: Translated your ANN to Japanese. If you needed, please use it.    Targetコインを発表 - 世界初の唯一のボーナス支払いクローズドエンド暗号基金 ICOは終わった！我々は間もなく取引所に自分自身を掲載する予定です。 Targetコインは、暗号化通貨市場における価格上昇と価格下落の両方でリスク調整後のリターンを生成するように設計された、エテリアルスマート契約に基づいて構築されたトークン化ロングショートファンドです  Targetコインは、投資家に保証された四半期毎のボーナスを支払います。   投資戦略  1.市場リスクと市場エクスポージャーを最小限に抑え、価格上昇と価格下落の両方で収益を生み出すバランスの取れたロング・ショート・ポートフォリオ  2.機械学習、技術分析、人工知能を使用して、過去のパターンを分析し、短期および長期の取引を行います。  3.有望な暗号化通貨への長期投資  市場リスクと価格リスクを組み合わせた注文を行うためのスプリットアルゴリズムの注文  5.異なる市場における流動性の推定とモデルを使用して確率に基づく短期的な価格変動を予測する  6.各国の複数の取引所における定量的裁定  7.市場リスクを米ドルに変換し、弱気市場でショートすることによりリスクを減らす。   利益分配  1. ICO投資家に0.75％の四半期毎のボーナスを保証する  2.利益の85％が四半期ごとに投資家に還元される  3. TGTCoinは年間運用手数料10％を請求します  4. TGTCoinは、純利益に対して15％の四半期業績報酬を請求する  ICOの詳細  1. TGTコインICOは、7月15日に開始し、8月31日に終了する。  2. TGTコインは、ICO中に20億コインを発行する  3. 400Mnコインは、ICO投資家より先に投資されます。  4.マネージメントチームが260のMnコインを保有  ICO期間中に調達された資金はすべてICOに保有され、後に監査可能な為替口座に保管されます。  ロードマップ -  TGTコインICOは7月15日に始まり、8月31日に終了し、9月10日に運営が開始されます。 第1四半期は9月10日から12月9日になります。第2四半期は、2017年12月10日から2018年3月9日までです。第3四半期は、2018年3月10日から2018年6月9日になります。第4四半期は、2018年6月10日から9月9日9月までです。四半期ごとに15日以内に配布されます。  以上、私が翻訳しました。

Author: Stowski
Title: [ANN] [ICO] Target Coin - World's FIRST And ONLY Bonus Paying Crypto Fund
Body: Long-time reader/lurker – first time poster here.  My issues here are:  1)   Lack of communication from the team following the close of the ICO. I appreciate that the trading platforms need to be set up and beginning to trade will take a lot of effort, however the team has been near silent on this since the ICO closed. I have emailed the team and not had a response on this. 2)   Unsold coins not being burned. This is very risky and as has been stated, seems a bit fishy. From my non-technical background, one possible explanation could be that these are being held for future ICOs? My understanding is that for individuals to buy into the fund in the future there will be other coin offerings? These may be therefore being held as a form of off market shares, that will be used for this purpose (companies on the FTSE are able to hold repurchased or issued shares for example) which would not impact the MCAP of the coin. 3)   Again back to the lack of communication. From what I previously read, details of the progress of the trading team needs to be communicated. This is a fast moving and volatile market, and informing investors every quarter (when the bonus is paid) is way too slow. To generate interest in the project, which would then help reflect value in the coin, there needs to be good PR about the healthy returns the team are generating. Again this needs to be on a regular basis and not just quarterly.  At this point it would be nice to have some official comms on the above issues, as well as an update on the website to confirm they have started trading.  From a scam point of view, if its true that the 400m included in the ICO total is from the 400m sold before the ICO, then there is surely more money to be made from running this as a business as stated. The additional investment from public investors is not significant in the grand scheme of things. 15% returns for the business could easily dwarf simple fraud if they run it well.  Still holding out hope that this is the real deal and not a scam. I don’t see anything Ive read so far to confirm for me one way or another.

Body: Many traders switch (partly) to crypto because of bigger volatility and margins. I love the idea to size up.  Just a couple of questions: 1. Are losses shares by investors? If profit is made after a loss, is the div based on net or just the profit? If the fund losse money is the 10% still paid out (10% is very much on the high side compared to approx 2 in normal hedgefund in my opinion)  2. After each quarter the max intrinsic value of the fund is the starting value because of fee and dividends?  3. More in delth info about track record, trading history would be appreciated.  4. High yields are definitely achievable. Could you please show the calculation for the RISK ADJUSTED return?  Looking forward to your answers!

Author: corleto
Title: [ANN] [ICO] Target Coin - World's FIRST And ONLY Bonus Paying Crypto Fund
Body: Sorry for the separate post. Just wanted to go through some numbers.  Example 1: the fund makes no money but just plays even. Fund intrinsic value = 80 million for 100% of the coins. Team gets 8 million (10%). This seems so weird to me. Does the fund have to make up the fee before dividends are started?  Example 2: the fund loses 40 million, fund intrinsic value = 40 million for 100% of the coins. Team gets 4 million? This seems very wrong for me. I see no mention of a high water mark. Why are you guys not working with a high water mark if you are so confident you will make money? I am sure this would ease the minds of potential investors.  Target Coin team is taking 13 % of the coins (80 * 0.13) 10.4 million worth of coins. Besides dividend on these coins 15% of total profit. With all this in mind I think 10% standard fee + no high water mark (investopedia is your friend if you dont know what this means) sends a wrong signal, conflicting with the confidence that the white paper sends.  With a normal, customary 1.5-2% fee and a high water mark this would be a no brainer for me as I believe the project has so much potential (although it would be nice to see some track record).  In the linked interview this comes along:  Does the team have a history of trading other assets?  The team as well as me have over 18 years of experience in trading and investing in equities, foreign exchange as well commodity markets. Our primary focus has been the concentrated equities portfolio which as we speak is up over 90% in the past 3 years.(i.e a CAGR of over 28% YoY)  90% over the past 3 years is not normal. Not a single hedgefund in the world makes 28% per year consistently.I am not saying scam at all! I actually believe Crypto gives a lot of opportunity for long/short funds, but I would like to see what the 70-200% RISK ADJUSTED return is based on/how it is calculated.  Finally, if 85% of profit is paid to token holders, and 15% is charged as a performance fee. You start with 80 mln, aim to be 500 mln in 2019, where does the other 420 mln come from? All the profits after 10% fee go to the team and the token holders. Perhaps I am missing something really simple, so please enlighten me :-)  Don't get me wrong, I am very disturbed by the ridiculous 10% fee and the lack of high water mark, but good traders in immature volatile markets have so much potential, I could still put my money in this ICO!

Author: corleto
Title: [ANN] [ICO] Target Coin - World's FIRST And ONLY Bonus Paying Crypto Fund
Body: One more thing, what is the 10% (8 million dollars) used for except for just salary? How many people are on the payroll except the 5-6 traders mentioned in the interview from the link?  Based on what I read Target Coin is using platforms like Polo, Kraken, Bitstamp, so there won't be huge development costs for a trading platform, or did I miss something?  It does sound 'a bit' self enriching to me, although good traders could actually be worth every dime.. Please convince me to invest, if you still want me after these few critical points of view and critical questions :-)

Author: TargetCoin
Title: [ANN] [ICO] Target Coin - World's FIRST And ONLY Bonus Paying Crypto Fund
Body: We don't think it will affect the sale drastically.

Author: TargetCoin
Title: [ANN] [ICO] Target Coin - World's FIRST And ONLY Bonus Paying Crypto Fund
Body: 1. The dividend is based on net profit. If the fund loses money, guaranteed bonus is paid out while the profits will be paid out in the next quarter. If the fund makes a net annual loss, we will not charge the entire 10% fee.  The 10% fees are higher for the first year because of the initial development, maintenance and research costs, which we shall revise after the first year.  2. Yes. Max intrinsic value of the fund is the starting value.  3. We have been trading in the traditional financial markets since years and have been fund managers previously managing a $25mn hedge fund - Alexandrite Capital.  Will share a snap of our crypto fund here in a separate post soon.  4. Risk adjusted return means minimising your downside in any trade. i.e Your average risk to reward ratio for each trade is 1:2 That means that for every dollar you risk, you make sure that you make at least $2. In that case, even if the fund manager is right for just 50% of the times, the fund will make (0.5*2 - 0.5*1)*100 = 50% returns.  At Target Coin we plan to maintain a minimum risk to reward ratio of 2.5 for each trade, making the downside minimum for each investors.

Author: TargetCoin
Title: [ANN] [ICO] Target Coin - World's FIRST And ONLY Bonus Paying Crypto Fund

Author: TargetCoin
Title: [ANN] [ICO] Target Coin - World's FIRST And ONLY Bonus Paying Crypto Fund
Body: Hi, we have invested personal money into the fund and got the coins at a discounted price. We do not charge management fee on the 400 Million tokens sold during the pre-ICO round.  Here is a link of our equity holdings -  http://imgur.com/a/TK8Hn  Our trading profits have been significantly higher. The founders have managed a long-short hedge fund Alexandrite Capital before and have beat the index for more than 6+ years. Will share an entire audited track record of our trading history soon.  We are investing a significant amount of money into building HFT crypto trading algorithms and TargetX. The 10% management fees are for the first year, which we will revise and reduce after the first year. We also give a guaranteed quarterly bonus which comes out to be 3% per year and 70-200% of annual risk adjusted returns.

Author: TargetCoin
Title: [ANN] [ICO] Target Coin - World's FIRST And ONLY Bonus Paying Crypto Fund
Body: Announcing Target Coin - World's FIRST and ONLY Bonus Paying Closed-End Crypto Fund       ICO is over! We will be listing ourselves on the exchanges soon.    Target Coin is a Tokenized long-short fund built on an Ethereum Smart Contract designed to generate risk adjusted returns on both price rise and price fall in the Crypto Currencies Market  Target Coin pays a guaranteed quarterly bonus to the investors.    Investment Strategy    1. A balanced long-short portfolio to minimise the market risk, market exposure and generate returns during both price rise and price fall  2. Using Machine Learning, Technical Analysis and Artificial Intelligence to analyse historical patterns and make short and long term trades.  3. Long-term investments in promising Crypto-Currencies  4. Order Splitting algorithm to place orders based on market impact combined by price-risk  5. Estimation of liquidities in different markets and using models to forecast short term price fluctuations based on probabilities  6. Quantitative Arbitrage across multiple exchanges in different countries  7. Hedging market risk by converting it into USDT and shorting during a bear market   Profit Sharing    1. A guaranteed quarterly bonus of 0.75% to the ICO investors  2. 85% of the profits will be given back to the investors every quarter  3. TGTCoin charges a 10% annual operations fee  4. TGTCoin charges a quarterly performance fee 15% on the net profits made   ICO Details    1. TGT Coin ICO launches on 15th July and ends on 31st August.  2. TGT Coin will issue 2 Bn Coins during the ICO  3.  400 Mn Coins are held by the pre-ICO investors.  4. Management Team holds 260 Mn Coins  All the funds raised during the ICO are held in the ICO and will be held in auditable exchange accounts afterwards. Details which will be shared with the investors.  Roadmap -    TGT Coin ICO starts on 15th July and ends on 31st August and the operations will begin on 10th September. The first quarter will be from 10th September to 9th December. The 2nd quarter will be from 10th December, 2017 to 9th March, 2018. The 3rd quarter will be from 10th March,2018 to 9th June, 2018. The 4th quarter will be from 10th June, 2018 to 9th September, 2018. The profits will be distributed within 15 days after the end of every quarter.
